data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.chText: （市、郡等的）政务委员会，地方议会
data.enText: a group of people who are elected to govern an area such as a city or county

data.chText: 市 / 郡 / 自治市 / 区政务委员会
政务委员会委员 / 会议
市政（或地方管理）服务机构
data.enText: the organization that provides services in a city or county, for example education, houses, libraries, etc.

data.chText: 市政工作人员 / 部门
（顾问、立法、研究、基金等）委员会
data.enText: a group of people chosen to give advice, make rules, do research, provide money, etc.

data.chText: 英国的艺术委员会向剧院提供资金。
data.enText: In Britain, the Arts Council gives grants to theatres.

data.chText: （尤指旧时讨论特定步骤的）协商会议
data.enText: (especially in the past) a formal meeting to discuss what action to take in a particular situation

data.chText: 国王于1330年10月14日至19日在诺丁汉召集协商会议。
data.enText: The King held a council at Nottingham from 14 to 19 October 1330.

a body serving in an administrative capacity
(Christianity) an assembly of theologians and bishops and other representatives of different churches or dioceses that is convened to regulate matters of discipline or doctrine

value.def: A council is a group of people who are elected to govern a local area such as a city or, in Britain, a county.

example.ex: The city council has voted almost unanimously in favour.
example.tran: 市政委员会几乎一致投票表示赞同。

example.ex: ...David Ward, one of just two Liberal Democrats on the council.
example.tran: 戴维·沃德，市政委员会中仅有的两名自由民主党人之一
对当地政务委员会会议的报道

value.def: Council houses or flats are owned by the local council, and people pay rent to live in them.

example.ex: There is a shortage of council housing...
Council tenants around the country are planning a mass lobby of Parliament.
example.tran: 全国各地的市政住房租户正在计划组建一个大的议会游说团。

value.tran: (房屋或公寓)地方政府出租的

value.def: Council is used in the names of some organizations.
In some organizations, the council is the group of people that controls or governs it.

example.ex: The permanent council of the Organization of American States meets today here in Washington.
example.tran: 美洲国家组织的常务委员们今天在华盛顿这里会面。
德意志联邦银行的中央委员会

value.def: A council is a specially organized, formal meeting that is attended by a particular group of people.

example.ex: President Najibullah said he would call a grand council of all Afghans...
example.tran: 纳吉布拉总统称他将召开阿富汗全民大会。

example.ex: The president also meets ministers at inter-ministerial councils held at the Elysée Palace.
example.tran: 总统还在爱丽舍宫接见了参加部长级会议的各部长。
